<title>USA: Cognizant sees $5.1 mln Q3 gain from TSI.</title>
<headline>Cognizant sees $5.1 mln Q3 gain from TSI.</headline>
<dateline>WESTPORT, Conn 1997-07-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cognizant Corp said Thursday it expects to report a $5.1 million pre-tax gain in the third quarter 1997 from the recent sale of stock offered in TSI International Software Ltd's initial public offering.</p>
<p>The IPO was completed July 2. TSI was an investment of Cognizant Enterprises, Cognizant's in-house venture capital business.</p>
<p>&quot;This demonstrates Cognizant's policy of returning value to our shareholders by monetizing properties in the venture portfolio which are not strategic to our core businesses,&quot; the company said. &quot;The transaction will generate $5.5 million in cash in the third quarter.&quot;</p>
</text>
